POWEROFF(1)                      User Commands                      POWEROFF(1)

NAME
       poweroff - power off the machine

SYNOPSIS
       poweroff [OPTION]

DESCRIPTION
       poweroff  instructs  the  system hardware to power off the machine.

OPTIONS
       -f, --force
              force immediate power-off; do not call shutdown

       -w, --wtmp-only
              don't actually power off; only write wtmp record (no-op)

       -d, --no-wtmp
              don't write wtmp record

       -n, --no-sync
              don't sync before power off

       --no-wall
              don't send wall message before powering off

       --help display this help and exit

NOTES
       halt, reboot, and poweroff are the same binary.  The command name
       (argv[0]) determines the action:

       halt      halts the system
       reboot    reboots the system
       poweroff  powers off the system

       The -f flag skips the graceful shutdown sequence.

AUTHORS
       LikeOS-64 project.

SEE ALSO
       halt(1), reboot(1), shutdown(1)

